features: 【High-Performance 130mm Full Function PWM Fan】The PCCOOLER 130mm case fan features an innovative turbocharging system with 10 reverse turbine teeth, which significantly increases air pressure and airflow. The full load air volume is about 76.85CFM and the air pressure is 2.46mm/H2O. Noise levels can be maintained between 18 and 29dB(A) even at full load. This CPU fan is fully compatible with downward-facing 120mm fan holes, making it easy to install in your computer case. The open fan inlet design allows for more air to flow into the fan, enabling efficient cooling. Supports PWM and automatically adjusts the fan speed according to the CPU temperature.

【Super Anti-Gravity Heat Pipe-250W TDP】PCCOOLER K6 CPU cooler utilizes exclusive direct contact technology, and the upgraded shape and layout of the heat pipes are more suitable for the heat dissipation layout of high-end CPU cores. It can challenge a TDP of up to 250W and effectively provide excellent heat dissipation. Equipped with excellent anti-gravity 6x6mm heat pipes, it has stronger capillary pumping force to effectively transfer heat from the CPU surface to the heatsink. Whether the heat pipes are horizontally or vertically placed, it has better cooling performance in PC cases.

【Premium Performance Thermal Paste】K6 CPU air cooler is equipped with PCCOOLER EX-90 high thermal conductivity thermal paste, which uses nano-diamond as the base material to effectively fill every gap and improve heat transfer efficiency. The ultra-high thermal conductivity is 14.8W/M.K, and it is very convenient to apply and wipe. Stable performance at -50 ℃ to 250℃. Improved performance of auxiliary radiator.

【Aluminum Heatsink for Efficient Heat Dissipation】The K6 CPU air cooler uses a 130mm pure aluminum fins with a cooling area of about 5900cm². This design effectively improves air pressure and enhances heat dissipation, resulting in a more stable system. The high-density aluminum fins and larger copper base ensure great thermal conductivity, while the optimized fin heat dissipation array ensures uniform heat dissipation. The surface of the PCCOOLER special cooling coating, the top cover to improve the overall beauty of the tower, with the design being in line with fluid mechanics to provide excellent heat dissipation performance.

【Support Sockets-New Design】Full metal center press point buckle. Support LGA1700/1200/1151/1150/1155/1156 and AMD AM4/AM5. Easy to install, durable, heat sink can be balanced pressure on the cpu. The CPU cooler base fits tightly to the cpu for increased heat transfer efficiency. More stable heat dissipation performance.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 28, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I got this for $19 and I got to say it’s definitely worth the money. It by itself before I add other fans in my pc was dropping it from 47c to 39c just by itself! With added fans dropped to an insane 28-30c while on stress test! And for being quite a big fan is stays very quiet even at high throttle.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 29, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Best Cooler for it's cost.
reviews.reviewText: I build and sell a lot of computers and normally do not leave reviews, but this cooler is more than well-deserved me leaving a review. This is the best cooler that I have ever bought at its price point. I highly recommend this cooler to anyone, and I will happily recommend it to anyone of my customers. If you are looking for a cooler and you are on a budget, there is no need to look any further because this cooler is for you. Its performance is just as amazing as its price. It has a solid mounting hardware that is way better than any other cooler at this price point and it includes everything you need. Solid affordable cooler without having to lose performance. I really hope that someone reads this review and decides to go with this cooler because I can promise you that you will not regret it in any way. I do not have one thing that I can complain about with this cooler.
